{{Notability|date=June 2010}} {{Refimprove|date=May 2009}} {{COI|date=May 2011}} {{Infobox OS | name = SchilliX | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | developer = currently JÃ¶rg Schilling and Fabian Otto | family = [[OpenSolaris]] | source_model = [[Open source]] | working_state = Current | latest_release_version = 0.7.2 | latest_release_date = {{release date|2010|09|22}} | kernel_type = | license = | website = http://schillix.berlios.de/ }} '''SchilliX''' is a [[Live CD]] [[operating system]] distribution based on [[OpenSolaris]]<ref>jimgris/admin/"unknown", [http://hub.opensolaris.org/bin/view/Main/downloads, "Other Distros"], "Oracle Corporation and/or its affiliates", 2010/03/26 02:53. Retrieved 2010/13/08 16:32.</ref>. It was released on 17 June 2005, three days after the first release of OpenSolaris. Its developers claim that it is the first OpenSolaris distribution. The initial developers were [[JÃ¶rg Schilling]], Fabian Otto, Thomas Blaesing, and Tobias Kirschstein.
The release version is 0.7.1i <small>(September 6, 2010)</small>, which uses the [[Illumos]]<ref>Anil Gulecha, [http://www.illumos.org/projects/site/wiki/FAQ, "FAQ"], "Illumos.org", 08/03/2010 10:13A.M. Retrieved 08/13/2010 16:21P.M.</ref> project for the build (once again being a first to make a release from a new open sourced build).
The current release is 0.7.2 which is the first OpenSolaris based redistributable distro that allows to compile the OpenSolaris source base (onnv / Illumos). The SchilliX project created a OSS replacement for the K&R [[C preprocessor|cpp]] needed by [[rpcgen]], [[dtrace]] and the assembler.
Future releases will be based upon the Schillix-ON<ref>http://developer.berlios.de/projects/schillix-on/</ref> project.
